<StarlightPage frontmatter={{ title: 'The Open-Source Coding Agent Landscape' , tableOfContents: false }}>

  <div class="wrap">

<header class="hero">
  <div class="eyebrow">Field Report · May 2026</div>
  <h1>The Open-Source Coding Agent Landscape</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Twelve months ago "AI coding tool" meant an editor with autocomplete. Today
    it means an autonomous agent that reads your repo, edits files, runs tests,
    drives a browser, and opens PRs. This is a snapshot of the open-source field
    as it stands today — who leads, who's interesting, and how to choose.
  </p>
  <div class="meta">
    <span>Compiled <b>2026-05-26</b></span>
    <span>Agents covered <b>11</b></span>
    <span>Scope <b>OSI-licensed projects, actively maintained</b></span>
    <span>Sources <b>15+ vendor docs, leaderboards, reviews</b></span>
  </div>
</header>

<section>
  <div class="h2-kicker">TL;DR</div>
  <h2>If you want to stop reading right now</h2>
  <p class="h2-sub">Three picks that cover the majority of use cases.</p>
  <div class="tldr-grid">
    <div class="tldr best" data-cf-change="ch-best-pick-green">
      <span class="best-flag">Top pick</span>
      <h3>Default pick</h3>
      <div class="pick">opencode</div>
      <p>Terminal-native, 75+ providers, LSP-aware, persistent sessions, MIT-licensed. The de-facto "Claude Code, but open" — and now the most-starred OSS coding agent on GitHub.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tldr">
      <h3>If you live in VS Code</h3>
      <div class="pick">Cline (or Roo&nbsp;Code)</div>
      <p>Cline is the safer mainline with Plan/Act, MCP, computer use. Roo Code forks it for richer multi-mode (Architect/Code/Debug/Ask) workflows.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tldr">
      <h3>If you want full autonomy</h3>
      <div class="pick">OpenHands</div>
      <p>Sandboxed multi-agent runtime, ~72% on SWE-bench Verified with Claude 4. Closest open analogue to Devin; deploys locally or on its own cloud.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

